{"votes": {"funny": 0, "useful": 0, "cool": 0}, "user_id": "UykLrbp-Wo4fR5nTRqU_HQ", "review_id": "PN6vTUkcIn9Ct7WTBFbTwA", "text": "i was in town for the weekend and came here with my sister. \"famous burgers\" is one of the signs you'll see when you walk up... but the burgers are probably only famous within the blacksburg/radford area. while looking over the menu, i saw that they had a burger with a fried egg and bacon... so considering my love for eggs i appropriately ordered it (called the hokie pokie burger) and i got it with sweet potato fries. my sister ordered the blazin bleu burger with curly fries. my burger was a little overcooked for my preference but the bacon and fried egg compensated for that, so overall the burger was okay. my sister's burger was an awesome cross between a burger and a buffalo wing. the sweet potato fries were extremely disappointing. the sad little strips of overcooked and under-seasoned sweet potato had me wishing i ordered the regular fries or the curly fries. the curly fries were pretty awesome, if only the sweet potato fries were equally as good. the service was really good so i have no complaints there, but the sanitation is a huge problem-- i used the restroom before we left and simply walking in disturbed a gross amount of flies that claimed residence at the toilet like rotting meat. if the bathroom standard is any indication of the cleanliness standard in the kitchen, the thought of returning makes me nervous.", "business_id": "Ij5vTLLpmulfCsK64jGGxw", "stars": 3, "date": "2012-06-13", "type": "review"}